    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="1271"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1271">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.63/50a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Special
                        Agent <persName type="to">Carothers</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 15, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Have examined the new order issued by Villa forfeiting mining property if not
                    worked to the satisfaction of the Secretary of Fomento. In view of the fact that
                    the law does not prescribe a certain amount of work but leaves the matter to the
                    discretion of officials without right of appeal to any court, you will please
                    bring the matter to the attention of Villa and say that it seems likely to
                    operate as confiscation of property. Ask for a suspension of the order in so far
                    as it affects foreigners, in order that we may more fully present the
                    objections.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
